gate: DONE
closed: 2026-06-03
owner: Daniil (DaniilDerkach)
pr: https://github.com/CT-CROP/CROP-search-hono/pull/332
note: |
  Merged to dev as part of combined PR#332 with A1/C1.
  getBrandDisplayName coverage for FRR/VNT/MCH/MAR verified by new tests.
  Brand facets (VNT/MCH slugs) verified in contract tests.
  Dan briefed via team channel (C3).
sprint: S06
track: C
task: C2
title: "feat(search): verify brand context in search results for all 4 V2 brands"
repos: [crop-search-hono]
priority: medium
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("we're now using alternate data sets")
  - S06-C1 (must run first — C2 validates the broader brand context, not just collision)
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN]

impact: |
  Beyond part-number collisions, every search result for a Ferris, Ventrac, McHale,
  or Marcrest part must correctly surface the brand so users know they're looking at
  the right product. If the brand label is missing or shows "Unknown", users can't
  trust the result.

description: |
  Validate that the brand context (manufacturer display name + code) is populated
  correctly in all search result shapes for the 4 new brands.

  Check 3 endpoints:
  1. `/api/search?q={ferrisPart}` — search adapter maps `manufacturer_codes` array
     to `brandCodes` in the UnifiedCatalogPart shape.
  2. `/api/parts/{ferrisPartId}` — part detail includes manufacturer name.
  3. `/api/autocomplete?q={ferrisQuery}` — autocomplete results include brand label.

  For each brand, verify `getBrandDisplayName(code)` returns the correct display name
  (not "UNK" or an empty string). This calls into `vocabulary-cache.ts` BRAND_REGISTRY.

  Also verify the `brand-extractor.ts` correctly identifies brand codes from Ferris/
  Ventrac/McHale parts (it uses `BRAND_KEYWORDS` map — check those brands are present
  or that they fall through safely if not in the CNH-family guard).

  Note: `brand-safety.ts` guards CNH family only. Ferris/Ventrac/McHale are not CNH
  family brands, so brand-safety.ts should not filter their content. Verify it does
  not accidentally block non-CNH brand results.

scope:
  in:
    - Verify getBrandDisplayName("FRR"), ("VNT"), ("MCH"), ("MAR") → correct names
    - Verify brand-extractor.ts does NOT misclassify Ferris parts as CNH-contaminated
    - Verify autocomplete includes brand token in highlights for new-brand queries
    - Spot-check: brand-safety.ts isAiBrandSafe returns true for non-CNH brand parts
      (they have no CNH-family brand mentions → safe by design)
    - Unit test: add FRR, VNT, MCH, MAR to `getBrandDisplayName` test coverage
  out:
    - Adding AI-generated descriptions to new brand parts (out of V2 scope)
    - Changing the CNH-family brand-safety scope (do not expand it)

invariants:
  - brand-safety.ts scope is CNH family only — do not modify it to include non-CNH brands
  - getBrandDisplayName must never return "UNK" for a registered brand code

acceptance:
  - getBrandDisplayName("FRR") === "Ferris" (unit test)   # FRR is canonical, not FER
  - getBrandDisplayName("VNT") === "Ventrac" (unit test)
  - getBrandDisplayName("MCH") === "McHale" (unit test)
  - getBrandDisplayName("MAR") === "Marcrest" (unit test — needs A1 first)
  - Autocomplete for "ferris" returns results with brand label "Ferris" (contract test)
  - No 500 errors on any search endpoint when queried with Ferris/Ventrac part numbers

dep: A1 (MAR display name not available until BRAND_REGISTRY updated), C1
output: vocabulary-cache.ts unit test additions + brand-extractor.ts spot-check fix (if needed)
